‚úÖ What is JRE (Java Runtime Environment)?
JRE stands for Java Runtime Environment. It provides everything needed to run Java programs ‚Äî but not develop them.

üîπ Key Points:
JRE = JVM + Core Java Libraries

It does not include tools like javac, javadoc, etc.

It‚Äôs mainly used by end-users or environments where you only need to run Java apps (not compile).

üì¶ JRE Contains:
| Component                                | Purpose                                                            |
| ---------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **JVM (Java Virtual Machine)**           | Executes `.class` files (Java bytecode)                            |
| **Core Libraries** (`rt.jar` or modules) | Provides essential Java APIs (like `java.lang`, `java.util`, etc.) |
| **Deployment Libraries**                 | For running applets, Java Web Start (older)                        |
| **Property Files & Configs**             | Timezones, security policies, etc.                                 |


