‚ö†Ô∏è Difference Between JDK and JRE:
| Feature            | **JDK**                | **JRE**            |
| ------------------ | ---------------------- | ------------------ |
| For                | Develop + Run          | Only Run           |
| Includes           | JRE + Compiler + Tools | JVM + Libraries    |
| Tools like `javac` | ‚úÖ Yes                  | ‚ùå No               |
| Used By            | Developers             | End-users, servers |


‚úÖ Real-World Use:
You install JDK to develop apps.

Your users install JRE (or it‚Äôs bundled in the app) to run those apps.

‚òëÔ∏è Since Java 11, Oracle no longer distributes a separate JRE ‚Äî everything is part of the JDK.